      "questionText": "A hockey puck slides across ice at a steady speed and then gradually slows down. Explain why the puck slows down in terms of forces.",
      "markScheme": {
        "answer": "Friction acts on the puck in the opposite direction to its motion. This is an unbalanced force. The resultant force decelerates the puck, causing it to slow down.",
        "steps": [
          { "mark": 1, "description": "Friction / air resistance acts on the puck" },
          { "mark": 2, "description": "There is no forward force, so forces are unbalanced" },
          { "mark": 3, "description": "The resultant force causes deceleration (slowing down)" }
        ],
        "commonErrors": [
          "Saying the puck runs out of force",
          "Not identifying friction as the cause"
        ]
      },
      "usedAsWorkedExample": false,
      "usedAsYourTurn": false
    },
